<ol><li>If a charged object is in<b> contact with the metal cap</b> of the electroscope, some of the charge on the object&nbsp;<b>transfers to the electroscope</b>.</li><li>As a result, the gold leaf and the metal stem attached to the cap&nbsp;<b>gain the same type of charge</b>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<b>the leaf rises</b>&nbsp;because it is repelled by the stem.</li></ol>